cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM 

Reasoning: The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks, specifically temporal grounding of event descriptions to videos. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a deep learning architecture, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper uses video datasets, which could also place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
